<div><h3>GEOG 373 - Seminar in Urban Geography </h3>  <hr>In this seminar we will consider fundamental geographical aspects of urban theory. Our goal is to undestand the ways that scholars have approached the study of cities, and to compare and contrast the epistemological assumptions underlying different approaches to &#8220;the urban.&#8221; We will critically evaluate major theoretical perspectives in light of their contribution to contemporary research. Open to doctoral students but masters students may request permission.<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> Offered every other year<br><br></div>		</td>
